Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
108 St Georges Terrace is recognised as a distinctive landmark defining the Perth skyline. This unique A+ grade property plays an important role in the city’s rich history. Architecturally significant, the sweeping 52-level tower and the heritage-listed Palace building are seamlessly integrated resulting in a property that is both distinguished and contemporary.

108 St Georges Terrace is a desirable address with state-of-the-art commercial space, tailor made for modern organisations.

The first class refurbishment of the Palace Hotel and Tower is now complete incorporating:

- Newly refurbished lobby and entry statement
- New destination control lift system & lift interiors
- Central plant upgrade
- Full floor refurbishments including ceilings, lighting, carpets and paint
- New bathrooms


108 St Georges Terrace offers:

- Premium workspace with abundant natural light.
- Conference facilities on both the ground floor and Level 51.
- Flexible floor plates providing various configuration possibilities.
- Multiple floors with the potential for inter-floor connectivity.
- Commanding views of the Swan River with the upper levels affording spectacular views of the Indian Ocean.
- A professional on-site team consisting of a full time concierge, general manager, administrator, facilities manager and senior security manager.
- Brand new end of trip facilities incorporating secure bicycle storage, change rooms, drying lockers and showers.
- Secure executive car parking bays over two levels.
- A café in the lobby and new restaurant Meat & Wine Co onsite.
